// Search 03 — does evolution exploit an environmental cline?
//
// packs/gradient-sieve.ron (2026-07-15) makes selection strength vary
// across space: one env-gated CULL with a raised information floor where
// field 0 is high. This search puts the flat-world sieve and the
// cline-world gradient-sieve in ONE pool and lets selection choose. The
// question (open half of the selection-pressure deliverable): do
// descendants keep the env-gated rule and exploit the gradient — e.g. by
// tuning thresholds so the mild west feeds survivors into the harsh
// east — or does the search strip the rule and revert to flat-world
// dynamics? Mutation operators never touch env_cond gates or the config's
// env spec (search v1 scope), so a lineage keeps its world's geography;
// what can change is every scalar around it, and whether the gated rule
// survives DropRule pressure.
//
// Instrument settings carried unchanged from search-02 (v1.1): sigma 0.6,
// 3 ops/child, screen 3k/every 100. Caps: gradient-sieve carries ~154k
// bonds at 3k (sieve ~166k), both inside the 200k screen cap; 600k
// confirmation cap per the horizon-sizing rule (expected ~2x screen bonds
// at 6k, x2 headroom). Fresh search seed; this is NOT a controlled
// comparison with search-02 (different seed pool by design — the control
// here is internal: two seed lineages, one pool).
//
// Budget: 2 seeds + 6 generations x 10 children = 62 screens at 3k, all
// sieve-class (expect ~90 min on the 4-core cloud box), top 2 confirmed
// at 6k.
//
//   genesis search --spec sweeps/search-03.ron --out <dir>
#![enable(implicit_some)]
(
    seed: 20260715,
    generations: 6,
    population: 10,
    survivors: 3,
    sigma: 0.6,
    mutations_per_child: 3,
    screen_ticks: 3000,
    every: 100,
    confirm_ticks: 6000,
    confirm_top: 2,
    bond_cap: 200000,
    confirm_bond_cap: 600000,
    seeds: [
        (
            name: "sieve",
            config: Some("configs/sieve.ron"),
            rules: "packs/sieve.ron",
        ),
        (
            name: "gradient-sieve",
            config: Some("configs/gradient-sieve.ron"),
            rules: "packs/gradient-sieve.ron",
        ),
    ],
)
